(Review writed with 7.6 hours gaming and all achievements unlocked - Jan 01st, 2017).

Out There Somewhere is a 8-bit portal game with a little of space invaders. You play with a space pilot who's crashlanded on an alien world, and you've found yourself inside a retro-tinged platformer in which each room works as a single puzzle, all to repair your spaceship. 


Pros:
- Challenging puzzles;
- Nice 8-bit portal game play.


Cons:	
- Few levels;
- Lame history;
- Few boring challenges;
- Hard achievements.


6,0/10.
